The paper presents a C++ library for solving large sparse linear systems of equations arising from discretization of partial differential equations on an unstructured grid. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Additionally, the library supports both shared and distributed memory computation, utilizes modern parallel processing technologies, and has minimal dependencies, which suggests that it may also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Modeling and Simulation (cs.MS), Computer Engineering (cs.CE), or Scientific Computing (cs.SC) sub-categories.
